Comedian Woli Arole has revealed he finds helping with house chores an exciting experience. Born Bayegun Oluwatoyin, the 31-year-old who was a guest on the TVC’s “Your View” on Friday explained his experience as the ‘untypical’ African man who delights in helping his wife with chores around the house. Describing himself as a comfortable plate-washer, Arole noted he’s also excited changing his son’s pampers and doing everything else together with his wife. He said: “There are times that it’s my wife that will be at home and you know, I’ll do some stuffs in the house. You’ll go out, she comes back and I realize that I’ve washed plates in the house. I still wash plates. I am a comfortable plate-washer. I am excited to wash plates. “I change pampers, I’m excited to change pampers. That’s the fact because, there’s beauty when we raise the child together.   You got it wrong on Tinubu, Ikeja constituents tell…     Ighalo reflects on ‘dream’ spell at Man United     MOSOP: Sane person must back Wike’s war against…   - Advertisement - “At times, there are some gist that are in the kitchen. If my wife is cooking, I follow her to the kitchen. So it’s like friendship. We have become friends. “So, the fact that we are fighting in the parlour, by the time we enter the kitchen; that fight will go down. Woli Arole, and wife Yemi Adeola, walked down the aisle on April 9, 2021 with friends and colleagues in the entertainment industry in attendance. Popular actor, Lateef Adedemeji, Asiri Comedy, Mr Macaroni, Pamilerin Adegoke, Testimony Jaga were among the groomsmen. After their traditional engagement, the love birds proceeded to do the white wedding thereafter, headed to the beachside for their reception. On January 2, the skit make taking to his Instagram page, announced the birth of their son. SPONSORED